  "original_title": "\u0b9c\u0bcb\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb8\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0ba9\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bae\u0bcd 4 \u0bae\u0ba3\u0bbf \u0ba8\u0bc7\u0bb0\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0bbf.\u0b90.\u0b9f\u0bbf. \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0b9a\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0ba3\u0bc8",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Johnston spent 4 hours in the CID. Investigation",
      "body_lines": [
        "The CID today (Jan. 24) held a four-hour interrogation of former Minister Johnston Fernando in connection with the outrageous attacks by government supporters on 'Maina Ko Gama' and 'Kota Ko Gama'.",
        "C.I.T. The CID said that a team led by Superintendent of Police Jayatilleke had conducted such investigations on him. The reports said.",
        "It is learned that Johnston Fernando, who went to the CID at 9.00 am today, was interrogated till 1.00 pm and obtained by ballot.",
        "Earlier on the 21st, the Fort Magistrate's Court had directed the CID to prosecute Johnston Fernando while he was out on bail in connection with the outrageous attacks by government supporters on 'Myna Ko Gama' and 'Kota Ko Gama'.",
        "It is pertinent to note that he has been ordered to appear before the CID by the court today and accordingly he has appeared there today and given his vote."
      ],
